@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_ns__Analogy> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_ns__Analogy> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Analogy> ;
    narr:childCount "7"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "2527c4e268800bf981f7076524c5e8f09cc961f0" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers the **analogies and metaphors** the narrative reaches for to make AI-collective-memory legible, spanning several registers. A developer register anchors the new to the familiar: organizational narrative that [branches like code](narr:StyleObs_analogy_git), evoking version-control intuitions already held by the target audience. A physical/embodiment register evokes coherence: AI identity as a [resonant body with a shape](narr:StyleObs_Analogy_Resonant) and sailing [telltales as worldview-drift detectors](narr:StyleObs_4). An organizational/economic register reframes expectations: [Google runs search on ~10-15 people](narr:StyleObs_GoogleAnalogy) to calibrate ICP scale assumptions, and the [cross-functional sales↔eng cascade](narr:Observation_CrossFunctionalCascade) to dramatize bidirectional immediacy. A humanizing register frames the tool as a [coworker that frees devs](narr:StyleObs_ScarletPMBurden) from PM-communication overhead, with the self-aware in-joke of [duplicating the customer's chief architect's brain](narr:StyleObs_Analogy_DuplicateBrain) grounding knowledge-extraction value in enterprise humor. Across all registers: analogy used to anchor an abstract product concept to something already held.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Observation_CrossFunctionalCascade> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_4> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_Analogy_DuplicateBrain> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_Analogy_Resonant> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_GoogleAnalogy> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_ScarletPMBurden> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_analogy_git> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "collective memory creates a living organizational worldview that evolves through intentional memory-saving and branches like code" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_analogy_git> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "AI identity as this sort of resonant body that has a shape to it" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_Analogy_Resonant> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "They serve as telltales. That's the right word. They serve as telltales" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_4> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "an organization like Google really only has like 10 or 15 people actually working on search" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_GoogleAnalogy> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Communicating vision etc with developers is half the point of all-hands, product process, putting context in tickets, etc and we're able to free devs now to focus on working and ask their coworker (the AI) for context" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_ScarletPMBurden> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "the constant joke in the enterprise customer, literally—I'm not kidding—is 'if only we could get AI to duplicate the customer's chief architect's brain.'" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_Analogy_DuplicateBrain> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "As soon as a salesperson, you know, gains additional context about a client, the engineer immediately benefits in the actual hands-on coding and vice versa." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Observation_CrossFunctionalCascade> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The telltales analogy is explicitly self-correcting mid-utterance — the speaker audibly searches for and then commits to the word — making it the one analogy marked as *found*, not pre-planned, which gives it a different rhetorical texture than the others." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_4> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The duplicate-brain in-joke operates as humor rather than argument, relying on enterprise-insider recognition; it may not travel to audiences outside that context, unlike the Google or git analogies which are broadly legible." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_Analogy_DuplicateBrain> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The coworker/liberation framing ('free devs') implicitly positions AI as replacing PM-to-dev communication load — a claim that could read as threatening to PMs rather than reassuring, depending on audience." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_ScarletPMBurden> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The resonant-body analogy operates in an embodiment/phenomenological register absent from all other analogies here, which are organizational or technical — it may serve a different persuasive function or audience." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#StyleObs_Analogy_Resonant> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}